audio_descriptions.notes:
Three figures make their way onto the dark stage; the director, the actress, and the man.
 
The director, a bald, ivory skinned man in a dark suit quickly looks through a roll of film.
 
On the opposite corner, the dark haired man dressed in a white suit wraps the actress in a white feather robe to match the ropes of pearls hanging around her neck. 

He guides her up the spiral staircase behind them.
 
The director notices and jumps across the stage. He holds her pleadingly but she resists. He takes the white feather coat hastily. Leaving her in a black shimmering gown. He points at the actress to leave. 
 
He points again, and she looks at him baffled. The actress looks back at the man and makes her way up the stairs. 
 
The director, looks away in visible distress. He looks back up and angrily points twice more at the pair still standing atop the staircase. The actress and the man disappear and exit the stage. 
 
The director stands alone in the dark space his hand still pointing.
 
A title reads “the director, having removed his beloved woman in an excess of jealousy, remains alone and without a diva.”
 
He presses his face to the white feather coat and holds it tightly, he looks out into the crowd with evident sadness in his eyes. 
 
A figure is seen entering the stage behind him. From the left, the director’s assistant approaches the director and he too touches the feather robe.
 
The figure is revealed; a bent over woman is seen on the other side of the stage. She sensually makes herself visible displaying a pearly complexion and two dark eyes to match her black hair and lips 
 
The director looks her down and up and she smiles.
 
A title reads “excuse me, are you the director?”
 
The director brings his hands to his face in the shape of a camera in agreeance. He looks around and makes his way to his chair. His assistant hands him his megaphone from behind.
 
The young actress with both hands clasping her chest awaits her direction
 
The director yells through his megaphone making a gestured command
 
The woman slowly faces the audience. She suddenly begins to wail soundlessly, pleading to the crowd with both hands in a fist, she throws her head back covering her face in despair. She then drops her hands and head, smiling at the director and concluding her performance.
 
The director gestures towards his chest and his face contorts into a second and more hasty demand.
 
The young actress  with both hands still on her chest readies herself, she turns to face the audience her mouth widens into a bright beam, she blows kisses into the crowd and wears a humbled expression as she wraps her arms around herself. She drops her smile and arms and concludes her second performance. 
 
The director points to the young actress, his chest, and back to the young actress.
 
He puts his megaphone to his mouth and a title flashes exclaiming the word tears.
 
The young actress looks back out into the audience, visibly displeased. Her face contorts into a second even more disconsolate wail, with both hands in a fist she pleads before she throws her head back in desperation. 
 
She drops the act looking proud and once again smiling to the director. The director looks behind him, and commands her once again. 
 
A title flashes and exclaims tears!
 
The young actress, places both hands on her chest, she flinches once… twice…  she throws herself on the ground with her face between her hands and looks up at the director
 
He looks back at her with a face of disgust 
 
He looks behind him and then proceeds to stand up, 

he begins to yell through the megaphone to the audience

The young actress, looks up at him frightened. 
 
A title flashes “tears, tears! If you have any respect for me at all you will give me your tears!
 
The young actress looks distraught. She reaches over to grab the megaphone. The director places one side to his ear as the actress softly speaks into the other.  
 
A title flashes “Please, let me play ‘Come Back, My Little One’"
 
The director slowly puts the megaphone down looking interested.
 
He puts the megaphone back to his mouth and mumbles something
 
The young actress, still sitting, readies herself, the director is crouched beside her 
 
Hey both stay still looking out into the distance

The actress looks nostalgic, even melancholic 

So does the director 
 
The director puts his arm around the young actress, and she cries with both hands still holding her chest
 
The director’s assistant is seen crying in the back.
 
A wide shot of the stage reveals the three characters are joined by two couples standing on each side of the stage looking in. The director hands the young actress a handkerchief and yells out into the megaphone
 
A title flashes and exclaims “so strong and so sad!”
